{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":811,"text":"So you go to the doctor\nand get some tests."},{"time":4674,"text":"The doctor determines\nthat you have high cholesterol"},{"time":7318,"text":"and you would benefit\nfrom medication to treat it."},{"time":10981,"text":"So you get a pillbox."},{"time":13505,"text":"You have some confidence,"},{"time":14728,"text":"your physician has some confidence\nthat this is going to work."},{"time":17689,"text":"The company that invented it did\na lot of studies, submitted it to the FDA."},{"time":21266,"text":"They studied it very carefully,\nskeptically, they approved it."},{"time":24397,"text":"They have a rough idea of how it works,"},{"time":26310,"text":"they have a rough idea\nof what the side effects are."},{"time":28787,"text":"It should be OK."},{"time":30864,"text":"You have a little more\nof a conversation with your physician"},{"time":33706,"text":"and the physician is a little worried\nbecause you've been blue,"},{"time":36693,"text":"haven't felt like yourself,"},{"time":38010,"text":"you haven't been able to enjoy things\nin life quite as much as you usually do."},{"time":41765,"text":"Your physician says, \"You know,\nI think you have some depression."},{"time":45792,"text":"I'm going to have to give\nyou another pill.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":48934,"text":"So now we're talking\nabout two medications."},{"time":51441,"text":"This pill also -- millions\nof people have taken it,"},{"time":54569,"text":"the company did studies,\nthe FDA looked at it -- all good."},{"time":58823,"text":"Think things should go OK."},{"time":60904,"text":"Think things should go OK."},{"time":63125,"text":"Well, wait a minute."},{"time":64588,"text":"How much have we studied\nthese two together?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":68630,"text":"Well, it's very hard to do that."},{"time":70954,"text":"In fact, it's not traditionally done."},{"time":73108,"text":"We totally depend on what we call\n\"post-marketing surveillance,\""},{"time":78650,"text":"after the drugs hit the market."},{"time":80996,"text":"How can we figure out\nif bad things are happening"},{"time":83868,"text":"between two medications?"},{"time":85249,"text":"Three? Five? Seven?"},{"time":87708,"text":"Ask your favorite person\nwho has several diagnoses"},{"time":90147,"text":"how many medications they're on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92530,"text":"Why do I care about this problem?"},{"time":94134,"text":"I care about it deeply."},{"time":95315,"text":"I'm an informatics and data science guy\nand really, in my opinion,"},{"time":99643,"text":"the only hope -- only hope --\nto understand these interactions"},{"time":103412,"text":"is to leverage lots\nof different sources of data"},{"time":106492,"text":"in order to figure out\nwhen drugs can be used together safely"},{"time":110072,"text":"and when it's not so safe."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112615,"text":"So let me tell you a data science story."},{"time":114690,"text":"And it begins with my student Nick."},{"time":116868,"text":"Let's call him \"Nick,\"\nbecause that's his name."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119272,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":120888,"text":"Nick was a young student."},{"time":122113,"text":"I said, \"You know, Nick, we have\nto understand how drugs work"},{"time":125216,"text":"and how they work together\nand how they work separately,"},{"time":127866,"text":"and we don't have a great understanding."},{"time":129812,"text":"But the FDA has made available\nan amazing database."},{"time":132241,"text":"It's a database of adverse events."},{"time":134321,"text":"They literally put on the web --"},{"time":135987,"text":"publicly available, you could all\ndownload it right now --"},{"time":139130,"text":"hundreds of thousands\nof adverse event reports"},{"time":142781,"text":"from patients, doctors,\ncompanies, pharmacists."},{"time":146565,"text":"And these reports are pretty simple:"},{"time":148338,"text":"it has all the diseases\nthat the patient has,"},{"time":151020,"text":"all the drugs that they're on,"},{"time":152811,"text":"and all the adverse events,\nor side effects, that they experience."},{"time":156653,"text":"It is not all of the adverse events\nthat are occurring in America today,"},{"time":160113,"text":"but it's hundreds and hundreds\nof thousands of drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":162715,"text":"So I said to Nick,"},{"time":164038,"text":"\"Let's think about glucose."},{"time":165888,"text":"Glucose is very important,\nand we know it's involved with diabetes."},{"time":169479,"text":"Let's see if we can understand\nglucose response."},{"time":173473,"text":"I sent Nick off. Nick came back."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176248,"text":"\"Russ,\" he said,"},{"time":178351,"text":"\"I've created a classifier that can\nlook at the side effects of a drug"},{"time":183487,"text":"based on looking at this database,"},{"time":185562,"text":"and can tell you whether that drug\nis likely to change glucose or not.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":189857,"text":"He did it. It was very simple, in a way."},{"time":191897,"text":"He took all the drugs\nthat were known to change glucose"},{"time":194556,"text":"and a bunch of drugs\nthat don't change glucose,"},{"time":196969,"text":"and said, \"What's the difference\nin their side effects?"},{"time":199881,"text":"Differences in fatigue? In appetite?\nIn urination habits?\""},{"time":204757,"text":"All those things conspired\nto give him a really good predictor."},{"time":207741,"text":"He said, \"Russ, I can predict\nwith 93 percent accuracy"},{"time":210313,"text":"when a drug will change glucose.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":211909,"text":"I said, \"Nick, that's great.\""},{"time":213349,"text":"He's a young student,\nyou have to build his confidence."},{"time":216269,"text":"\"But Nick, there's a problem."},{"time":217683,"text":"It's that every physician in the world\nknows all the drugs that change glucose,"},{"time":221667,"text":"because it's core to our practice."},{"time":223729,"text":"So it's great, good job,\nbut not really that interesting,"},{"time":227475,"text":"definitely not publishable.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":229030,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":230068,"text":"He said, \"I know, Russ.\nI thought you might say that.\""},{"time":232642,"text":"Nick is smart."},{"time":234149,"text":"\"I thought you might say that,\nso I did one other experiment."},{"time":237047,"text":"I looked at people in this database\nwho were on two drugs,"},{"time":239999,"text":"and I looked for signals similar,\nglucose-changing signals,"},{"time":244445,"text":"for people taking two drugs,"},{"time":246093,"text":"where each drug alone\ndid not change glucose,"},{"time":251686,"text":"but together I saw a strong signal.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":254170,"text":"And I said, \"Oh! You're clever.\nGood idea. Show me the list.\""},{"time":257343,"text":"And there's a bunch of drugs,\nnot very exciting."},{"time":259621,"text":"But what caught my eye\nwas, on the list there were two drugs:"},{"time":263577,"text":"paroxetine, or Paxil, an antidepressant;"},{"time":267756,"text":"and pravastatin, or Pravachol,\na cholesterol medication."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271936,"text":"And I said, \"Huh. There are millions\nof Americans on those two drugs.\""},{"time":276243,"text":"In fact, we learned later,"},{"time":277513,"text":"15 million Americans on paroxetine\nat the time, 15 million on pravastatin,"},{"time":283569,"text":"and a million, we estimated, on both."},{"time":286767,"text":"So that's a million people"},{"time":288045,"text":"who might be having some problems\nwith their glucose"},{"time":290522,"text":"if this machine-learning mumbo jumbo\nthat he did in the FDA database"},{"time":293752,"text":"actually holds up."},{"time":295030,"text":"But I said, \"It's still not publishable,"},{"time":296981,"text":"because I love what you did\nwith the mumbo jumbo,"},{"time":299301,"text":"with the machine learning,"},{"time":300571,"text":"but it's not really standard-of-proof\nevidence that we have.\""},{"time":305618,"text":"So we have to do something else."},{"time":307231,"text":"Let's go into the Stanford\nelectronic medical record."},{"time":310131,"text":"We have a copy of it\nthat's OK for research,"},{"time":312219,"text":"we removed identifying information."},{"time":314581,"text":"And I said, \"Let's see if people\non these two drugs"},{"time":317108,"text":"have problems with their glucose.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":319242,"text":"Now there are thousands\nand thousands of people"},{"time":321473,"text":"in the Stanford medical records\nthat take paroxetine and pravastatin."},{"time":324956,"text":"But we needed special patients."},{"time":326779,"text":"We needed patients who were on one of them\nand had a glucose measurement,"},{"time":331400,"text":"then got the second one and had\nanother glucose measurement,"},{"time":334873,"text":"all within a reasonable period of time --\nsomething like two months."},{"time":338512,"text":"And when we did that,\nwe found 10 patients."},{"time":342592,"text":"However, eight out of the 10\nhad a bump in their glucose"},{"time":347154,"text":"when they got the second P --\nwe call this P and P --"},{"time":349823,"text":"when they got the second P."},{"time":351157,"text":"Either one could be first,\nthe second one comes up,"},{"time":353743,"text":"glucose went up\n20 milligrams per deciliter."},{"time":356614,"text":"Just as a reminder,"},{"time":357796,"text":"you walk around normally,\nif you're not diabetic,"},{"time":360145,"text":"with a glucose of around 90."},{"time":361528,"text":"And if it gets up to 120, 125,"},{"time":363628,"text":"your doctor begins to think\nabout a potential diagnosis of diabetes."},{"time":367102,"text":"So a 20 bump -- pretty significant."}]},{"cues":[{"time":370601,"text":"I said, \"Nick, this is very cool."},{"time":373616,"text":"But, I'm sorry, we still\ndon't have a paper,"},{"time":375693,"text":"because this is 10 patients\nand -- give me a break --"},{"time":378296,"text":"it's not enough patients.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":379565,"text":"So we said, what can we do?"},{"time":380895,"text":"And we said, let's call our friends\nat Harvard and Vanderbilt,"},{"time":383895,"text":"who also -- Harvard in Boston,\nVanderbilt in Nashville,"},{"time":386506,"text":"who also have electronic\nmedical records similar to ours."},{"time":389351,"text":"Let's see if they can find\nsimilar patients"},{"time":391395,"text":"with the one P, the other P,\nthe glucose measurements"},{"time":394695,"text":"in that range that we need."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396787,"text":"God bless them, Vanderbilt\nin one week found 40 such patients,"},{"time":401766,"text":"same trend."},{"time":403804,"text":"Harvard found 100 patients, same trend."},{"time":407448,"text":"So at the end, we had 150 patients\nfrom three diverse medical centers"},{"time":411753,"text":"that were telling us that patients\ngetting these two drugs"},{"time":415074,"text":"were having their glucose bump\nsomewhat significantly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418317,"text":"More interestingly,\nwe had left out diabetics,"},{"time":421151,"text":"because diabetics already\nhave messed up glucose."},{"time":423492,"text":"When we looked\nat the glucose of diabetics,"},{"time":425754,"text":"it was going up 60 milligrams\nper deciliter, not just 20."},{"time":429760,"text":"This was a big deal, and we said,\n\"We've got to publish this.\""},{"time":433236,"text":"We submitted the paper."},{"time":434439,"text":"It was all data evidence,"},{"time":436574,"text":"data from the FDA, data from Stanford,"},{"time":439081,"text":"data from Vanderbilt, data from Harvard."},{"time":441051,"text":"We had not done a single real experiment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":444495,"text":"But we were nervous."},{"time":446201,"text":"So Nick, while the paper\nwas in review, went to the lab."},{"time":449955,"text":"We found somebody\nwho knew about lab stuff."},{"time":452441,"text":"I don't do that."},{"time":453858,"text":"I take care of patients,\nbut I don't do pipettes."},{"time":457420,"text":"They taught us how to feed mice drugs."},{"time":460864,"text":"We took mice and we gave them\none P, paroxetine."},{"time":463302,"text":"We gave some other mice pravastatin."},{"time":465834,"text":"And we gave a third group\nof mice both of them."},{"time":469893,"text":"And lo and behold, glucose went up\n20 to 60 milligrams per deciliter"},{"time":473863,"text":"in the mice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475058,"text":"So the paper was accepted\nbased on the informatics evidence alone,"},{"time":478240,"text":"but we added a little note at the end,"},{"time":480158,"text":"saying, oh by the way,\nif you give these to mice, it goes up."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483081,"text":"That was great, and the story\ncould have ended there."},{"time":485613,"text":"But I still have six and a half minutes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487634,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":490465,"text":"So we were sitting around\nthinking about all of this,"},{"time":493304,"text":"and I don't remember who thought\nof it, but somebody said,"},{"time":496063,"text":"\"I wonder if patients\nwho are taking these two drugs"},{"time":499288,"text":"are noticing side effects\nof hyperglycemia."},{"time":502865,"text":"They could and they should."},{"time":504761,"text":"How would we ever determine that?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":507551,"text":"We said, well, what do you do?"},{"time":509018,"text":"You're taking a medication,\none new medication or two,"},{"time":511622,"text":"and you get a funny feeling."},{"time":513184,"text":"What do you do?"},{"time":514359,"text":"You go to Google"},{"time":515534,"text":"and type in the two drugs you're taking\nor the one drug you're taking,"},{"time":518907,"text":"and you type in \"side effects.\""},{"time":520534,"text":"What are you experiencing?"},{"time":522239,"text":"So we said OK,"},{"time":523414,"text":"let's ask Google if they will share\ntheir search logs with us,"},{"time":526494,"text":"so that we can look at the search logs"},{"time":528351,"text":"and see if patients are doing\nthese kinds of searches."},{"time":530940,"text":"Google, I am sorry to say,\ndenied our request."},{"time":534819,"text":"So I was bummed."},{"time":535994,"text":"I was at a dinner with a colleague\nwho works at Microsoft Research"},{"time":539184,"text":"and I said, \"We wanted to do this study,"},{"time":541149,"text":"Google said no, it's kind of a bummer.\""},{"time":543053,"text":"He said, \"Well, we have\nthe Bing searches.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":546195,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":550805,"text":"Yeah."},{"time":552096,"text":"That's great."},{"time":553271,"text":"Now I felt like I was --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":554446,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":555470,"text":"I felt like I was talking to Nick again."},{"time":558437,"text":"He works for one of the largest\ncompanies in the world,"},{"time":561085,"text":"and I'm already trying\nto make him feel better."},{"time":563315,"text":"But he said, \"No, Russ --\nyou might not understand."},{"time":565784,"text":"We not only have Bing searches,"},{"time":567308,"text":"but if you use Internet Explorer\nto do searches at Google,"},{"time":570672,"text":"Yahoo, Bing, any ..."},{"time":572587,"text":"Then, for 18 months, we keep that data\nfor research purposes only.\""},{"time":576254,"text":"I said, \"Now you're talking!\""},{"time":578214,"text":"This was Eric Horvitz,\nmy friend at Microsoft."}]},{"cues":[{"time":580436,"text":"So we did a study"},{"time":582155,"text":"where we defined 50 words\nthat a regular person might type in"},{"time":586798,"text":"if they're having hyperglycemia,"},{"time":588424,"text":"like \"fatigue,\" \"loss of appetite,\"\n\"urinating a lot,\" \"peeing a lot\" --"},{"time":593210,"text":"forgive me, but that's one\nof the things you might type in."},{"time":596001,"text":"So we had 50 phrases\nthat we called the \"diabetes words.\""},{"time":598815,"text":"And we did first a baseline."},{"time":600902,"text":"And it turns out\nthat about .5 to one percent"},{"time":603630,"text":"of all searches on the Internet\ninvolve one of those words."},{"time":606636,"text":"So that's our baseline rate."},{"time":608402,"text":"If people type in \"paroxetine\"\nor \"Paxil\" -- those are synonyms --"},{"time":612569,"text":"and one of those words,"},{"time":613808,"text":"the rate goes up to about two percent\nof diabetes-type words,"},{"time":618722,"text":"if you already know\nthat there's that \"paroxetine\" word."},{"time":622191,"text":"If it's \"pravastatin,\" the rate goes up\nto about three percent from the baseline."},{"time":627171,"text":"If both \"paroxetine\" and \"pravastatin\"\nare present in the query,"},{"time":631585,"text":"it goes up to 10 percent,"},{"time":633278,"text":"a huge three- to four-fold increase"},{"time":636763,"text":"in those searches with the two drugs\nthat we were interested in,"},{"time":640176,"text":"and diabetes-type words\nor hyperglycemia-type words."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644216,"text":"We published this,"},{"time":645505,"text":"and it got some attention."},{"time":646995,"text":"The reason it deserves attention"},{"time":648797,"text":"is that patients are telling us\ntheir side effects indirectly"},{"time":653133,"text":"through their searches."},{"time":654313,"text":"We brought this\nto the attention of the FDA."},{"time":656475,"text":"They were interested."},{"time":657768,"text":"They have set up social media\nsurveillance programs"},{"time":661398,"text":"to collaborate with Microsoft,"},{"time":663173,"text":"which had a nice infrastructure\nfor doing this, and others,"},{"time":665991,"text":"to look at Twitter feeds,"},{"time":667297,"text":"to look at Facebook feeds,"},{"time":669037,"text":"to look at search logs,"},{"time":670372,"text":"to try to see early signs that drugs,\neither individually or together,"},{"time":675305,"text":"are causing problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676918,"text":"What do I take from this?\nWhy tell this story?"},{"time":679116,"text":"Well, first of all,"},{"time":680347,"text":"we have now the promise\nof big data and medium-sized data"},{"time":684408,"text":"to help us understand drug interactions"},{"time":687350,"text":"and really, fundamentally, drug actions."},{"time":689794,"text":"How do drugs work?"},{"time":691231,"text":"This will create and has created\na new ecosystem"},{"time":694091,"text":"for understanding how drugs work\nand to optimize their use."},{"time":698303,"text":"Nick went on; he's a professor\nat Columbia now."},{"time":700986,"text":"He did this in his PhD\nfor hundreds of pairs of drugs."},{"time":705082,"text":"He found several\nvery important interactions,"},{"time":707623,"text":"and so we replicated this"},{"time":708861,"text":"and we showed that this\nis a way that really works"},{"time":711459,"text":"for finding drug-drug interactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714282,"text":"However, there's a couple of things."},{"time":716040,"text":"We don't just use pairs\nof drugs at a time."},{"time":719110,"text":"As I said before, there are patients\non three, five, seven, nine drugs."},{"time":723981,"text":"Have they been studied with respect\nto their nine-way interaction?"},{"time":727647,"text":"Yes, we can do pair-wise,\nA and B, A and C, A and D,"},{"time":731879,"text":"but what about A, B, C,\nD, E, F, G all together,"},{"time":736189,"text":"being taken by the same patient,"},{"time":737975,"text":"perhaps interacting with each other"},{"time":740117,"text":"in ways that either makes them\nmore effective or less effective"},{"time":743919,"text":"or causes side effects\nthat are unexpected?"},{"time":746275,"text":"We really have no idea."},{"time":748126,"text":"It's a blue sky, open field\nfor us to use data"},{"time":751906,"text":"to try to understand\nthe interaction of drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":754848,"text":"Two more lessons:"},{"time":756242,"text":"I want you to think about the power\nthat we were able to generate"},{"time":760465,"text":"with the data from people who had\nvolunteered their adverse reactions"},{"time":765200,"text":"through their pharmacists,\nthrough themselves, through their doctors,"},{"time":768493,"text":"the people who allowed the databases\nat Stanford, Harvard, Vanderbilt,"},{"time":772184,"text":"to be used for research."},{"time":773929,"text":"People are worried about data."},{"time":775398,"text":"They're worried about their privacy\nand security -- they should be."},{"time":778609,"text":"We need secure systems."},{"time":779784,"text":"But we can't have a system\nthat closes that data off,"},{"time":783214,"text":"because it is too rich of a source"},{"time":785990,"text":"of inspiration, innovation and discovery"},{"time":789985,"text":"for new things in medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792494,"text":"And the final thing I want to say is,"},{"time":794312,"text":"in this case we found two drugs\nand it was a little bit of a sad story."},{"time":797693,"text":"The two drugs actually caused problems."},{"time":799638,"text":"They increased glucose."},{"time":801137,"text":"They could throw somebody into diabetes"},{"time":803607,"text":"who would otherwise not be in diabetes,"},{"time":805925,"text":"and so you would want to use\nthe two drugs very carefully together,"},{"time":809124,"text":"perhaps not together,"},{"time":810299,"text":"make different choices\nwhen you're prescribing."},{"time":812663,"text":"But there was another possibility."},{"time":814533,"text":"We could have found\ntwo drugs or three drugs"},{"time":816901,"text":"that were interacting in a beneficial way."},{"time":819616,"text":"We could have found new effects of drugs"},{"time":822352,"text":"that neither of them has alone,"},{"time":824536,"text":"but together, instead\nof causing a side effect,"},{"time":827053,"text":"they could be a new and novel treatment"},{"time":829502,"text":"for diseases that don't have treatments"},{"time":831408,"text":"or where the treatments are not effective."},{"time":833439,"text":"If we think about drug treatment today,"},{"time":835858,"text":"all the major breakthroughs --"},{"time":837634,"text":"for HIV, for tuberculosis,\nfor depression, for diabetes --"},{"time":841955,"text":"it's always a cocktail of drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844809,"text":"And so the upside here,"},{"time":846563,"text":"and the subject for a different\nTED Talk on a different day,"},{"time":849436,"text":"is how can we use the same data sources"},{"time":852053,"text":"to find good effects\nof drugs in combination"},{"time":855640,"text":"that will provide us new treatments,"},{"time":857839,"text":"new insights into how drugs work"},{"time":859715,"text":"and enable us to take care\nof our patients even better?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":863525,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864715,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}